[4B] India
Date: Fri 13 Aug 2021 4:29 AM IST
Source: Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/covid-cases-stay-near-40k-falling-sluggishly-in-august/articleshow/85290030.cms


Fresh COVID-19 cases remained above 20 000 for the 3rd day running in Kerala while Maharashtra's count topped 6000 for the 1st time in 5 days even as daily cases in India continued to decline marginally while staying close to the 40 000 mark.

India has seen a steady, although painfully slow, fall in daily COVID-19 cases so far in August [2021] after a spike in the last week of July [2021]. The 7-day rolling average of daily cases, which had risen to 40 832 on [1 Aug 2021], stood at 37 719 on [Wed 11 Aug 2021], the lowest since [25 Jul 2021].

India was likely to record its 2nd straight day of 40 000-plus new cases. After logging 41 649 on [Wed 11 Aug 2021], daily cases on [Thu 12 Aug 2021] stood at 39 248, with updates from Manipur, Tripura, and Jharkhand still awaited. The 3 states had together reported more than 850 cases on the previous day.

Kerala recorded 21 445 fresh infections, continuing to account for more than 50% of all new cases in the country. The state reported a test positivity rate of 14.73%, up from 14.49% on [Wed 11 Aug 2021], indicating that the virus was continuing to rage in the region.

While Karnataka reported 1857 new cases, the highest count in the state came from the Dakshina Kannada district bordering Kerala.

Maharashtra logged 6388 fresh cases, the daily tally having crossed 6000 for the 1st time since [7 Aug 2021]. The state also recorded more than 200 deaths (208) for the 1st time in August [2021].

The spurt in fatalities took the day's COVID-19 toll in the country to 570, the highest in 6 days. Kerala recorded 160 deaths, followed by 67 in Odisha, 33 in Tamil Nadu, and 30 in Karnataka.

