[4C] Nepal
Date: Thu 12 Aug 2021 3:47 PM NPT
Source: The Himalayan Times [abridged, edited]
https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/nepal-reports-2473-fresh-covid-cases-32-deaths-in-24-hours


Nepal's coronavirus caseload reached 725 769 on [Thu 12 Aug 2021] with 2473 more people testing positive for the infection in the past 24 hours.

Meanwhile, the total coronavirus recoveries stand at 677 377 with 2294 discharges logged today [12 Aug 2021].

On the other hand, the countrywide COVID-19 mortality toll increased to 10 212 with 32 more fatalities.

As per the latest data provided by the health ministry, 15 462 total tests were conducted in the last 24 hours of which 10 806 were PCR tests while 4656 were antigen tests. With this, a total of 3 729 109 PCR tests have been carried out to date [12 Aug 2021].

Similarly, antigen tests have confirmed 787 positive cases in the past 24 hours. The total number of single-day infections from both the RT-PCR and antigen tests amount to 3260.

Nepal's COVID-19 recovery rate stands at 93.3%, while the fatality rate stands at 1.5%. The country's active COVID-19 case count currently is 38 180.

So far, a total of 7 515 766 people have received the coronavirus vaccine across the country, of which 4 593 526 have received the 1st dose while only 2 922 240 individuals have been inoculated with both doses and are fully vaccinated.

In the same time frame, 811 infections were reported in the capital city, while Lalitpur and Bhaktapur reported 192 and 130 cases respectively.

Currently, there are 441 individuals in various quarantine facilities across Nepal.

On [Wed 11 Aug 2021], Nepal's coronavirus caseload had reached 723 296 with 2616 more people testing positive for the infection.

