Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data by country, area, or territory for 13 Aug 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20AUG13_1628971662.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 36.3% of daily case numbers and 35.6% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 79.62 million cases. The USA reported over 141 000 cases over the last 24 hours followed by Brazil (32 443), Mexico (22 711), and Argentina (11 397). 10 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, while 2 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 24.6% of daily case numbers and 13.9% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 62.12 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (2 cases), Switzerland (6 cases), and Kazakhstan, among others. 18 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 8 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 9.1% of daily case numbers and 8.6% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 13.44 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (39 049) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Pakistan, Libya, Tunisia, and UAE. Saudi Arabia reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 3.9% of daily case numbers and 7.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.24 million cases. South Africa (14 271), reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours followed by Kenya, Eswatini, and Mozambique. Ethiopia, Algeria, Nigeria, Zimbabwe, Zambia, and Senegal reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Cameroon, Botswana, Uganda, Gabon, and Congo, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 9.3% of daily case numbers and 8.5% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.19 million cases. Malaysia, reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 21 000 cases), followed by Japan, Philippines, Vietnam, South Korea, French Polynesia, Mongolia, Fiji, and Cambodia.

- The South East Asia region reported 16.4% of the daily newly reported cases and 25.8% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 39.70 million cases. India is dominant reporting over 40 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Indonesia (30 788), Thailand (23 418), Bangladesh (8465), Myanmar (3456), and Nepal (2763). Additionally, Sri Lanka and Maldives have not reported any cases in the last many days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 13 Aug 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

